Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.00,0:00:05.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Hello it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.00,0:00:05.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你好 我是Scott Manley
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.84,0:00:09.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Today I want to talk to you about weapons grade stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.84,0:00:09.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}今天我想和你谈谈些武器级的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.36,0:00:13.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now the term weapons grade has entered into popular parallels to the extent
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.36,0:00:13.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在“武器级”一词已经拥有了许多热门的同义 以至于
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.84,0:00:18.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that we are currently talking about weapons grade memes being deployed against Wall Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.84,0:00:18.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们目前正在讨论的是 那些热门针对华尔街部署的武器级备忘录
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.03,0:00:23.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm gonna point out that you should not confuse this with military grade
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.03,0:00:23.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我想指出的是 你不应该将其与“军工级”相混淆
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.27,0:00:25.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is a completely meaningless term
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.27,0:00:25.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那是一个完全没有意义的术语
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.39,0:00:29.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}generally added to Amazon listings to sell them to a certain type of person.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.39,0:00:29.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一般是加在亚马逊的商品目录里 以把它们卖给某类人
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.08,0:00:35.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now weapons grade refers to weapons-grade material needed to make nuclear weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.08,0:00:35.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 武器级是指制造核武器所需的武器级材料
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.23,0:00:42.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And these basically set down constraints as to the isotope ratios for the material
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.23,0:00:42.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这些基本上对材料的同位素比作出了限制
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.55,0:00:45.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so that they can be used to easily build bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.55,0:00:45.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以至于 它们可以被轻易地用来制造炸弹
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.34,0:00:48.90,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And the reason why of course we're interested in this is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.34,0:00:48.90,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而当然 我们对此感兴趣的原因是
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.94,0:00:54.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you want to keep that kind of material under control to stop it to stop nuclear proliferation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.94,0:00:54.61,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你想把这种材料控制住 以阻止核扩散
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.21,0:01:01.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now the origin of these terms I believe goes back to like the 1950s
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.21,0:01:01.07,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 这些术语的起源我相信可以追溯到20世纪50年代
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.10,0:01:06.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where the US is starting to collaborate on nuclear science with other nations
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.10,0:01:06.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在那时 美国开始在核科学方面与其他国家进行合作
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.55,0:01:10.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they're looking at what level of uranium enrichment they can share
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.55,0:01:10.97,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而他们正在研究 他们可以分享哪种级别的浓缩铀
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.99,0:01:14.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and there's this document that was published that figured out that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.99,0:01:14.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并有这样的文件被公布 其认为
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.39,0:01:18.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}for research reactors they shouldn't allow anything more than 20%
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.39,0:01:18.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对于研究用反应堆 他们不应该允许分享任何超过20％的浓缩铀
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.59,0:01:24.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so 20% becomes the transition from low enriched uranium to highly enriched uranium.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.59,0:01:24.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 20%成为低浓缩铀到高浓缩铀的转变
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.51,0:01:26.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And weapons grade is like 80%.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.51,0:01:26.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而武器级则是80%
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.43,0:01:30.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Yeah depending upon the material, you've got different rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.43,0:01:30.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是的 根据材料的不同 你有不同的规定
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.36,0:01:35.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}For uranium it's all about the isotopic ratio of uranium-235
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.36,0:01:35.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对于铀 这些规定基本都是关于铀235的同位素比
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.93,0:01:39.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is the stuff that actually explodes and drives the chain reaction
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.93,0:01:39.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它也就是实际爆炸和驱动链式反应的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.74,0:01:45.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and uranium-238 which sort of generally sits on the sidelines and doesn't do very much useful stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.74,0:01:45.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}和铀238的同位素比 后者通常坐在一边 并不做非常有用的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.06,0:01:57.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now in nature you've only got 0.7% uranium-235 in regular uranium and the rest is 99.3% uranium-238
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.06,0:01:57.19,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 在自然中 普通铀中只有0.7%的铀235 而其余的99.3%是铀238
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.93,0:02:03.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so it is possible to make a nuclear reactor using just this regular material
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.93,0:02:03.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 对于建造一个核反应堆来说 只使用这种自然材料是做得到的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.96,0:02:07.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but you have to have a lot of moderators to slow down the neutrons
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.96,0:02:07.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但你必须有大量的慢化剂 来减缓中子的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.50,0:02:13.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and get them to pay attention to the 235 and stop all those 238s from getting in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.50,0:02:13.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而让其专注与铀235发生裂变反应 并阻止铀238对反应的妨碍
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:17.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But if you go through a process of enrichment
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:17.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 如果你通过一个浓缩的过程
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.03,0:02:21.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where you exploit the very small differences in mass between these two atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.03,0:02:21.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是你利用这两种原子之间非常小的质量差异
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.33,0:02:27.42,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you enhance the concentration of the uranium-235
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.33,0:02:27.42,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并且你提高了铀235的浓度
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.80,0:02:31.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}then your reaction gets easier and easier to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.80,0:02:31.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么你的反应就会变得越来越容易进行
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.54,0:02:35.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now for the first atom bomb drop from a plane that was a little boy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.54,0:02:35.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 第一颗从飞机上投下的原子弹是小男孩
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.92,0:02:40.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it was made with material that was on average 80% enriched.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.92,0:02:40.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而它是用平均浓度为80%的浓缩铀材料制成的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.08,0:02:44.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I say on average because apparently large parts of it were 90% enriched
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.08,0:02:44.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我说平均 因为很明显 它的很大一部分是90%的浓缩铀
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.48,0:02:47.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but there was some part which was only 50% enriched.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.48,0:02:47.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但也有一些部分浓缩度只有50%
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.39,0:02:52.67,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}A lot of these details are uh still somewhat classified.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.39,0:02:52.67,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些细节在某种程度上仍然是保密的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:58.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So it's relatively easy to make an atom bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:58.48,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 制造原子弹相对来说是比较容易的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.48,0:03:05.37,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}if you have enough for uranium at 80 concentration enrichment, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.48,0:03:05.37,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果你有足够量的浓度为80%的浓缩铀 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:12.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}As you get to lower and lower levels of enrichment you need larger and larger critical masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:12.33,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当你达到越来越低的浓缩水平时 你需要越来越大的临界质量
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.92,0:03:19.23,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And like in theory I believe you can make 20% low enriched uranium go off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.92,0:03:19.23,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而就像在理论上 我相信你可以使20%的低浓缩铀爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.92,0:03:25.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The point is that you you want to restrict these very high things from being available to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.92,0:03:25.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}问题是 你想限制这些非常高浓缩度的东西被提供给世界
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:32.99,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and generally the only stuff that's really kept around these days is highly enriched.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:32.99,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而一般来说 现在唯一真正限制的东西是高浓缩的铀
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:37.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The highly enriched uranium is used in very limited number of cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:37.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}高浓缩铀被用于非常有限的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.08,0:03:41.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Sometimes used in submarine reactors for example
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.08,0:03:41.45,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}例如 其有时用于潜艇的核反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.48,0:03:46.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where you want to get high power density and the least amount of stuff getting in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.48,0:03:46.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在那里 你想获得高功率密度 并且碍事的东西越少越好
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.22,0:03:51.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay so plutonium.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.22,0:03:51.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好吧 那么钚
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.28,0:03:55.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now plutonium is actually what's used in most atom bombs these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.28,0:03:55.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 钚实际上是现在大多数原子弹中使用的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.14,0:03:56.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.14,0:03:56.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它好得多
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.48,0:03:59.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It has much lower critical mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.48,0:03:59.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它的临界质量低得多
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.12,0:04:02.30,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's a lot harder to work with for various reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.12,0:04:02.30,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}由于各种原因 它更难处理
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.54,0:04:04.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But it's generally become the thing of choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.54,0:04:04.69,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但它成为了一般首选的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.70,0:04:07.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now plutonium isn't a natural material.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.70,0:04:07.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 钚并不是一种天然材料
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:08.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's made in a reactor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:08.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它是在反应堆中制造的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.78,0:04:13.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's actually made where you have a regular chain reaction going with uranium-235
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.78,0:04:13.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它实际上是在一个与铀235的常规链式反应中制造的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.41,0:04:16.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that uranium-238 that isn't doing anything useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.41,0:04:16.29,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而那没有做任何有用的事的铀238
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.52,0:04:20.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It will frequently absorb a neutron that will increase the mass to 239
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.52,0:04:20.83,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它会经常吸收一个中子 将其质量增加到239
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.86,0:04:25.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then it'll undergo a series of radioactive decays and you'll get plutonium-239.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.86,0:04:25.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后 它将经历一系列的放射性衰变 而你会得到钚239
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.97,0:04:29.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So this is how they made the plutonium for the first atom bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.97,0:04:29.29,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以 这就是他们为第一颗原子弹制造钚的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.33,0:04:32.05,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They built these reactors that didn't produce power.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.33,0:04:32.05,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们建立了这些不生产电力的反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.45,0:04:34.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They actually took power from the power grid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.45,0:04:34.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们实际上是从电网上获取电力
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:37.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But they sustained this reaction
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:37.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但他们维持这个反应
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:39.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they were able to take the materials out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:39.95,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并且 他们能够从中获取材料
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.40,0:04:42.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}reprocess them, extract the plutonium
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.40,0:04:42.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}重新处理它们 提取出钚
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.80,0:04:46.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that was the material was used to make the trinity device
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.80,0:04:46.07,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这些材料被用来制造三位一体装置
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.10,0:04:48.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which was the first atom bomb ever detonated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.10,0:04:48.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是有史以来引爆的第一颗原子弹
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.90,0:04:52.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And of course later the fat man which was dropped over Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.90,0:04:52.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 后来在长崎上空投放的胖子也是如此
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.62,0:04:58.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So with plutonium yeah the 239 is the stuff that explodes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.62,0:04:58.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 对于钚来说 钚239是会爆炸的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.82,0:05:03.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but as it turns out the other isotopes pretty much all explode too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.82,0:05:03.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但事实证明 其他同位素也几乎都会爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.85,0:05:10.06,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}However with a material in the reactor it's not just plutonium-239 you get.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.85,0:05:10.06,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然而 对于反应堆中的材料 你得到的不仅仅是钚239
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.09,0:05:14.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You get other isotopes produced because you can't exactly control the series of reactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.09,0:05:14.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你会得到其他同位素的产生 因为你不能完全控制一系列的反应
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.80,0:05:19.63,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Sometimes that 239 will absorb another neutron and it'll become plutonium-240.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.80,0:05:19.63,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有时 钚239会吸收另一个中子 变成钚240
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.13,0:05:23.42,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Sometimes there are other reactions that will produce plutonium-238
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.13,0:05:23.42,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有时还有其他反应会产生钚238
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:27.25,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is the stuff that is used in spacecraft for power generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:27.25,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那也就是在航天器中用于发电的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.67,0:05:31.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The problem is that both of these materials have drawbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.67,0:05:31.97,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}问题是 这两种材料都有缺点
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.89,0:05:38.13,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The plutonium-240 is just as valid as a weapons material
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.89,0:05:38.13,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}钚240与武器级的材料一样有效
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:41.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but it will undergo spontaneous fission more often
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:41.69,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但它会更经常地发生自发裂变
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:45.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that means that it can trigger the reaction early.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:45.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这意味着它可能会提前触发反应
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.39,0:05:48.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And I don't mean early as in when the bombs are sitting around doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.39,0:05:48.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而我所说的提前 并不是炸弹无所事事的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.35,0:05:53.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean that during the process of collapsing your material down into a critical mass
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.35,0:05:53.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我的意思是 在把你的材料压缩到一个临界质量的过程中
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.64,0:05:55.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you want to squish it as small as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.64,0:05:55.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你想把它压得越小越好
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.97,0:05:58.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it takes a finite amount of time to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.97,0:05:58.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这需要有限的时间来做到这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:01.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But if you've got too much plutonium-240 there
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:01.19,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 如果你有太多的钚240在那里
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.52,0:06:05.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it can actually trigger the reaction while you are still squeezing things down
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.52,0:06:05.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它实际上可以在物质仍在压缩时触发反应
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.84,0:06:11.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that means you never reach your peak density and the bomb explodes with less energy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.84,0:06:11.85,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这意味着你永远不会达到你的峰值密度 并且炸弹爆炸的能量较小
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.88,0:06:13.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because it has less density.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.88,0:06:13.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为它的密度较小
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.40,0:06:15.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So that's one problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.40,0:06:15.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以这就是一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.92,0:06:18.41,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The plutonium 240 by the way is the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.92,0:06:18.41,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}顺便说一下 钚240就是
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.49,0:06:21.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}why they couldn't build a simple gun-type device
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.49,0:06:21.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为什么他们不能制作一个简单的枪式装置的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.67,0:06:26.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where you shoot one slug into another and that makes your critical mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.67,0:06:26.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你把一个弹头射入另一个弹头 而这造就了你的临界质量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:29.91,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}With that they figured out the barrel needed to be way too long
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:29.91,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}使用这个方式 他们发现其枪管所需的长度太长了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.91,0:06:33.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because plutonium's chance of predetonation was too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.91,0:06:33.33,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为钚的预爆几率太高
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.28,0:06:41.09,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So with weapons grades plutonium you make sure there's no more than 6.5% plutonium-240.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.28,0:06:41.09,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 对于武器级钚 你要确保其中的钚240含量不超过6.5%
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.55,0:06:45.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The 238 as I said is used in spacecraft because it's radioactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.55,0:06:45.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}钚238 正如我所说 其被用于航天器 因为它具有放射性(α衰变)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:46.25,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It generates a lot of heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:46.25,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它会产生大量的热量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.30,0:06:51.15,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So having too much heat in the device that you want to use is a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.30,0:06:51.15,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 在你想使用的设备中 有太多的热量是一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.18,0:06:53.01,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It means you have to somehow get rid of that heat
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.18,0:06:53.01,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这意味着你必须以某种方式摆脱这些热量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:56.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or it will damage components damage your explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:56.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}否则它就会损坏部件 损坏你的爆炸物
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:07:03.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the weapons grade material has less than one half of a% of plutonium-238 in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:07:03.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 武器级材料中的钚238含量不到0.5%
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.72,0:07:10.99,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So that's your thing 93% plutonium-239 with 7% other stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.72,0:07:10.99,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 这些就是你的东西 93％的钚239和7％的其他东西
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:12.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's weapons grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:12.94,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些就是武器级的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:16.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But again that's just what is easy to work with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:16.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但再一次 这些也只是易于处理的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.98,0:07:22.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}As you get more and more other isotopes in there it is still possible to build weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.98,0:07:22.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当你有越来越多的其他同位素在那里 它仍然有可能制造武器
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.34,0:07:25.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and in 1962 Britain was working with the US
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.34,0:07:25.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在1962年 英国与美国合作
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.78,0:07:29.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they came along with some reactor grade material that had
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.78,0:07:29.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并且英国带来了一些反应堆级的材料 其中有
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.91,0:07:33.58,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but it's believed it was about 15% other isotopes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.91,0:07:33.58,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但据说有大约15%的其他同位素
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.02,0:07:38.21,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they used that to build a bomb to demonstrate that was possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.02,0:07:38.21,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而他们用它来制造炸弹 以证明这是可能的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.23,0:07:39.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And it yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.23,0:07:39.89,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且它确实可以
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.93,0:07:43.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It was a little weaker I believe it was only about 10 kilotons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.93,0:07:43.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它的威力有点弱 我相信它只有大约10千吨
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:44.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But this is all classified.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:44.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这些都是机密
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.69,0:07:47.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The exact numbers here are totally classified.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.69,0:07:47.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这里的确切数字是完全保密的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.90,0:07:50.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And I'm just guessing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.90,0:07:50.29,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而我只是在这里猜测
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.70,0:07:52.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So it is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.70,0:07:52.96,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以用它是可能的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:56.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I think there's another calculation I saw that said that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:56.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我想我看到的另一个计算方法 是说
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.22,0:08:05.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}going from like 5% other isotopes to 15% other isotopes cuts your weapon yield by a factor of 10
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.22,0:08:05.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从5%的其他同位素到15%的其他同位素 会使你的当量减少10倍
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.36,0:08:09.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then going from 15% to 25% cuts it by another factor of 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.36,0:08:09.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后从15%增加到25% 再减少10倍的产量
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.50,0:08:11.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But that's not to say that it's impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.50,0:08:11.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这并不是说 用它们制造武器是不可能的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.57,0:08:14.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it just gets harder and your yields get lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.57,0:08:14.83,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它只是变得更难 并且你的当量变得更低
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.34,0:08:19.65,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the thing about making the plutonium in the reactor is that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.34,0:08:19.65,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 关于在反应堆中制造钚的事情是
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.67,0:08:22.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because you've got all these other side reactions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.67,0:08:22.48,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为你有所有这些其他的副反应
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.86,0:08:27.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}reactors are designed to make fuel or fissile material for nuclear weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.86,0:08:27.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那些为了制造核武器的燃料或裂变材料 而设计的反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.14,0:08:32.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}will generally only keep the rods in the reactor for a couple of weeks
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.14,0:08:32.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}通常只会将反应棒保留在反应堆里几个星期
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.34,0:08:34.43,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then take them out for reprocessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.34,0:08:34.43,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后把它们拿出来进行再加工
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.82,0:08:38.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But that in many reactor designs pressurized water designs means
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.82,0:08:38.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 在许多反应堆的设计中 比如压水式反应堆的设计意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.78,0:08:42.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}shutting the entire reactor down letting it cool down and then taking the rods out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.78,0:08:42.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}关闭整个反应堆 让它冷却下来 然后把反应棒取出
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.74,0:08:48.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Whereas the reactors that were used to generate the plutonium for the first weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.74,0:08:48.14,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而用于生产第一批用于核武器的钚的反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.39,0:08:52.37,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they had this sort of continuous flow system where you pushed the rods in at one end
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.39,0:08:52.37,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们有这种连续流通的系统 也就是你在一端将反应棒推入
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.41,0:08:56.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it was horizontal and as you pushed it in it pushed the rods out the back
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.41,0:08:56.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它是水平的 当你把它推入时 它会把里面的反应棒从后面推出来
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:09:01.57,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so they could keep the fuel in the reactor for only a limited amount of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:09:01.57,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 他们可以让燃料(反应棒)只在反应堆中停留有限的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.32,0:09:05.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}When you have the fuel sitting in the reactor for years
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.32,0:09:05.45,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当你把燃料放在反应堆里好几年的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.75,0:09:09.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it generates much much more of these other reactants
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.75,0:09:09.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它会产生更多的这些其他反应物
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.57,0:09:12.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and so the material is not considered weapons grade
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.57,0:09:12.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以因此 该材料不被认为是武器级
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.14,0:09:14.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}unless you can somehow remove these.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.14,0:09:14.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}除非你能以某种方式消除这些其他的反应物
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:20.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yeah that's again why you want to control reprocess nuclear material
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:20.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以再一次 这也是为什么你要控制核材料的再加工
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:23.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but equally it becomes very hard to build an atom bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:23.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但同样地 制造原子弹也变得非常困难
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.80,0:09:26.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because of the problems of pre-detonation and heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.80,0:09:26.89,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为有预爆炸和热量的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.36,0:09:30.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now there is one other nuclear material that's worth mentioning
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.36,0:09:30.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 还有一种值得一提的核材料
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.80,0:09:33.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that is uranium-233.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.80,0:09:33.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而那就是铀233
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.25,0:09:38.65,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's another isotope o'f uranium that in many ways is actually better than uranium-235.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.25,0:09:38.65,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那是另一种铀的同位素 其在许多方面实际上比铀235更好
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.69,0:09:42.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You actually need a lower critical mass of uranium-233.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.69,0:09:42.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你实际上只需要一个较低临界质量的铀233
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.74,0:09:46.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So uranium-233 comes from thorium reactors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.74,0:09:46.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}铀233来自于钍反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.60,0:09:51.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}When thorium-232 which is the most common isotope absorbs a neutron
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.60,0:09:51.85,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当钍232(也就是最常见的同位素) 吸收了一个中子后
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:54.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it transmutes into uranium-233
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:54.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它会转化为铀233
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:58.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then that's the stuff that actually undergoes fission in these reactors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:58.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后那就是在这些反应堆中实际发生裂变的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.06,0:10:02.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And again yeah you can use this in bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.06,0:10:02.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}再说一遍 是的 你可以在炸弹中使用这个
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.72,0:10:05.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It was been tested. The US has tested a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.72,0:10:05.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它已经被测试过了 美国已经用它测试了一种武器
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.19,0:10:07.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I believe India might have tested a weapon with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.19,0:10:07.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我相信印度可能也已经用它试验了一种武器
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.32,0:10:12.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The problem is that again it's a material produced in a reactor
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.32,0:10:12.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}再一次 问题是 这是一种在反应堆中产生的材料
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.43,0:10:16.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you have other materials other isotopes produced.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.43,0:10:16.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且你还有其他材料和其他同位素的产生
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.56,0:10:21.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And the biggest problem is uranium-232 that can result
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.56,0:10:21.17,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而最大的问题是其可能产生铀232
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.86,0:10:24.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and on its own it's fine right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.86,0:10:24.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而它本身是没问题的 对吗
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.64,0:10:26.06,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It'll actually undergo fission too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.64,0:10:26.06,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它实际上也会发生裂变
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.43,0:10:30.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But it decays into a whole bunch of other decay products
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.43,0:10:30.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但它会衰变成一大堆其他的衰变产物
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.11,0:10:33.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which produce a lot of gamma rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.11,0:10:33.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这产生了大量的伽马射线
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.95,0:10:40.30,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And so I believe anything more than about 50 parts per million of uranium-232 in your sample
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.95,0:10:40.30,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以我相信 如果你的样品中铀232的含量超过百万分之五十
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.64,0:10:44.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}makes it very hard to work with because of the amount of gamma radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.64,0:10:44.17,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它就会变得很难处理 因为它有大量的伽马辐射
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.20,0:10:48.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You have to move to like shielded glove box or remote manipulation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.20,0:10:48.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你会必须转而使用有防护罩的手套箱或者是进行遥控操作
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.47,0:10:50.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}rather than simply glove boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.47,0:10:50.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而不是使用普通的手套箱
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:54.53,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So this 50 parts per million requirement is really hard to achieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:54.53,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以这个百万分之五十的要求真的很难实现
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.85,0:10:59.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And it's one of the reasons why thorium reactors are usually cited by their proponents
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.85,0:10:59.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这也是为什么 钍反应堆通常被其支持者赞扬
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:03.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}as being a very low proliferation risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:03.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其作为一个核扩散风险非常低的反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.10,0:11:07.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yeah that's that's what weapons grade means.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.10,0:11:07.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以 是的 这就是武器级的含义
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.34,0:11:10.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's all about the isotope ratios of all these different materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.34,0:11:10.97,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这都是关于所有这些不同材料的同位素比率
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:16.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There's probably other fissile materials where the concept of weapons grade has been considered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:16.94,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可能还有其他裂变材料也被认为是武器级的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.97,0:11:23.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You can make a bomb with neptunium, californium, americium. I had never had to know how to pronounce that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.97,0:11:23.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你可以用镎 锎 镅制作炸弹 我从来没有想过要知道它们该如何发音
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.30,0:11:26.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But it's a thing that makes stuff explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.30,0:11:26.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但它们是一种能让东西爆炸的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.89,0:11:29.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yes now you all know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.89,0:11:29.51,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以 是的 现在你们都知道了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.51,0:11:33.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Weapons grade material. Make sure you've got your percentages laid out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.51,0:11:33.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}武器级材料 确保你已经把你要的百分比安排好了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.76,0:11:36.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Otherwise you won't get the boom boom that you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.76,0:11:36.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}否则 你不会得到你想要的爆炸声
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.39,0:11:38.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm Scott Manley. Fly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.39,0:11:38.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我是Scott Manley 切记 注意飞行安全
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.00,0:11:57.67,1080P-sgbd-4s,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[Music]
